==English==

===Noun===

#state of connectedness and interdependence of all phenomena

===Translation===

*Vietnamese: Tiếp Hiện.  
Literally:  being in touch with, continuing (Tiếp) 
+ realizing, making it here and now (Hiện)

===Etymology===
First employed by Vietnamese Zen Buddhist teacher Thich Nhat Hanh (b. 1926). In 1966 Thich Nhat Hanh founded the Order of Interbeing.

===Antonyms===
* separateness; separation
* alienation